Season pork with salt and black pepper. In a large Dutch oven brown pork in olive oil, about 6 minutes per side. Remove pork and set aside. Reduce heat to low and add onion and garlic. Cook until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes. Add RED GOLD(R) or REDPACK(R) WHOLE PEELED TOMATOES, sugar, orange zest, and chicken broth. Return pork to the Dutch oven and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour. Stir in carrots and mint, season with salt and black pepper. Cook about 15 minutes longer. Remove and discard orange strip and serve over noodles.